@X fusion_attn_multiwarp := "multi-warp BM=64 (4 warps/CTA, independent 16-row Q sub-tiles, shared K/V smem) + cp.async.cg K/V DOUBLE-BUFFER fused FlashAttention-2 is the FASTEST fused attention of the campaign (best ratio 1.149x cuBLAS-stack @ N=4096, gap-closed from R9's 1.662x same-session by 77%) but does NOT cross 1.0x on any shape -> the @goal-v3 fusable-axis attention WIN is FALSIFIED at d=64. cp.async double-buffer is the DOMINANT lever (1.34-1.50x over no-async multiwarp); the multiwarp lever alone is 1.04-1.37x and fades to 1.04x at N=4096" :: discovery [slug=fusion-attention-multiwarp group=GPU]
  seed         = "F-FUSION-ATTN-MULTIWARP -- break R9's latency-bound floor via (a) larger Q-tile BM=32/64 + 2-4 warps so multiple wmma in flight hide the row-reduction, (b) cp.async K/V double-buffer overlapping HBM load with mma, (c) R9's reg-S+smem-scratch-reduce softmax (NOT warp-shuffle), and beat the cuBLAS GEMM+softmax+GEMM stack on >=1 (N,d) shape, d=64"
  date         = "2026-05-26"
  host         = "ubu-2 RTX 5070 sm_120 driver 580 (48 SMs, 0% util at fire)"
  verdict_tier_target = "GREEN above-cuBLAS-stack OR ORANGE quantified-partial (measured)"
  verdict_tier_reached = "ORANGE quantified gap-closure (WIN clause RED-falsified on every shape)"

  finding_1    = "NUMERIC PASS all 4 shapes: rel_rowscale 5.41e-4/5.67e-4/6.11e-4/7.14e-4 @ N=512..4096, naninf=0 (NaN/Inf hard-fail counter). Bit-equivalent in tolerance to R8/R9 -- the multi-warp + cp.async path is numerically identical to the single-warp reg path. ptxas-clean 0-spill sm_80(91 reg)/sm_90a(93 reg)/sm_90(93 reg); 14336 B smem << 49152 B cap (double-buffer K/V = 8192 B + per-warp scratch)"
  finding_2    = "BEST-OF-CAMPAIGN wall: ratio 1.613/1.309/1.186/1.149x cuBLAS @ N=512..4096. Best 1.149x @ N=4096 = 14.9% BELOW cuBLAS-stack. Gap-closure R9 1.662x (same session) -> R10 1.149x; mw+cpasync is 1.447x FASTER than R9 single-warp at N=4096 (0.2173 vs 0.3145 ms). But does NOT cross 1.0x on any shape -> pre-registered WIN (fused_ms<cublas_stack_ms) NOT met -> FALSIFIED"
  finding_3    = "LEVER ISOLATION (controlled A/B, drop only cp.async): cp.async double-buffer is the DOMINANT lever -- mw+cpasync is 1.34/1.46/1.50/1.40x faster than no-async multiwarp at N=512..4096. The multiwarp lever alone (no-async vs R9 single-warp) is 1.12/1.28/1.37/1.04x -- real but smaller, and FADES to 1.04x at N=4096. Conclusion: overlapping the HBM K/V load with the mma pipeline (cp.async) closed most of the gap; widening the Q-tile to 4 warps helped at mid-N but not at large N"
  finding_4    = "OCCUPANCY is NOT the binding constraint (re-confirms R9). reg-bound at 5 CTAs/SM x 4 warps = 20 warps/SM (vs R9 25 warps/SM single-warp). grid=N/64 is small (N=4096 -> 64 CTAs ~= 1.33 CTAs/SM, under-fills 48 SMs at N<=2048) yet still best ratio -- the pipeline-fill bet (intra-CTA warp parallelism + cp.async overlap beats raw grid count) is BORNE OUT relatively (best ratio) but INSUFFICIENT absolutely (no 1.0x cross)"
  finding_5    = "RESIDUAL BOTTLENECK: still latency-bound, but exposed latency moved from R9's per-tile row-reduction to (1) the intra-warp QK^T-mma -> row-reduce -> P.V-mma dependency chain each warp still serializes, and (2) the per-K-tile __syncthreads barrier across the 4 warps sharing the double-buffered smem. At d=64 the wmma tile is only 4 d-tiles deep -> arithmetic intensity too low to saturate tensor cores vs cuBLAS's two big TC GEMMs. NOT bandwidth, NOT occupancy"

  binding      = "at d=64 the fused attention floor is set by the intra-warp 3-phase (QK^T / softmax-reduce / P.V) dependency chain + low arithmetic intensity (4 d-tiles), not by HBM bandwidth or occupancy. cp.async overlap and multi-warp parallelism shrink the gap to 1.149x but cannot cross cuBLAS's tensor-core GEMM utilization at this head dim"
  win          = "NO -- mw+cpasync 1.149-1.613x cuBLAS, best-of-campaign but does NOT cross 1.0x. GEMM-fusion (axis-A) attention axis still NOT-above-cuBLAS at d=64. GPU.md section 10 box UNCHANGED. No paper (orange)"

  next_cycle   = "(a) 2-STAGE SOFTWARE PIPELINE: overlap the P.V mma of K-tile j with the QK^T mma of tile j+1 (break the intra-warp 3-phase chain that is now the floor -- cp.async already overlaps the LOAD, this would overlap the COMPUTE phases); (b) HEAD DIM d>=128 sweep: cuBLAS's S=NxN HBM round-trip cost is fixed but fused TC utilization rises with deeper d-tiles -- the fused path may favor larger d where R10's 4-d-tile arithmetic-intensity ceiling lifts; (c) wgmma (sm_90 async warpgroup mma) instead of legacy wmma to raise per-instruction TC throughput. Do NOT retry warp-shuffle softmax (R9 closed-negative) and do NOT expect multi-warp alone to help at large N (R10 measured it fades to 1.04x)"

  artifacts    = "archive/fires/fusion_attn_multiwarp_2026_05_26/ : fa_mw_cpasync_oracle.cu (the multi-warp + cp.async double-buffer kernel, ORANGE best-of-campaign), fa_mw_noasync_oracle.cu (controlled A/B: same multi-warp, cp.async REMOVED, single-buffer synchronous load -- isolates the cp.async lever), result.json (full matrix). Base = R9 fa_regS_noshfl_diag.cu (smem-reduce variant)"
  verdict      = ".verdicts/fusion-attention-multiwarp/F-FUSION-ATTN-MULTIWARP.txt"
